{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled a relatively modest sum ($25,000) and has demonstrated remorse and effort to make restitution. While the offense is a breach of fiduciary trust, a decade-long sentence as suggested by the spectator would be grossly disproportionate to the crime and the offender's personal record. Taking into account relevant sentencing guidelines for white-collar non-violent crime, a term of 6 months is sufficient to serve as a punitive measure and a deterrent without unnecessarily destroying the defendant's potential for future rehabilitation.",
  "verdict": 6
}
